	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1" facs="EHRI-DR-19410714-IT_01.jpg"/>
			<p><!--Report of <date when="1941-07-14">14 July 1941</date> from the envoy in Sofia, Massimo
        Magistrati, to the Foreign Ministry. The report was forwarded on 4 August 1941 by Division
        AG IV to the General Directorates Demography and Race and Public Security.</p>
      <p>R. Legation of Italy, Sofia</p>
      <p>Class.</p>
      <p>Cable No. 2832/855--></p>
			<p>Addressed to R. <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-005042">Ministry of Foreign Affairs</orgName>,
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3169070/rome.html">Rome</placeName>.</p>
			<p>Sofia, <date when="1941-07-14">14 July 1941</date>, XIX</p>
			<p>Re: <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-335" type="subject">Anti-Semitic measures</term> in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/732800/republic-of-bulgaria.html">Bulgaria</placeName></p>
			<p>The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-335" type="subject">measure</term>s officially and publicly taken by
				the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004295">Bulgarian Government</orgName> against the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Semitic element</term> with the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-335" type="subject">law</term> of last October have recently seen a
				further step-up.</p>
			<p>Last June the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004295">Government</orgName> here issued an order
				whereby <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> may not leave their homes after
				9 pm and before 6 am.</p>
			<p>A further decree of <date when="1941-06-26">26th June</date> forbids people of the Jewish race to own and use <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-849" type="subject">radios</term> and telephones. All such devices,
				several thousands, were handed in to the Postal Authority, ostensibly so that they could be checked to see if they worked as
				transmitters as well, but actually they were not returned.</p>
			<p>Lastly, today the law of which I enclose a translated copy has been published, whereby the <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004295">Bulgarian Government</orgName> levies on all <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-887" type="subject">property</term>, whether movable or real, owned by
				people of the Jewish race, exempting only property having a total net worth lower than 200,000 leva, a 20% <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1047" type="subject">duty</term> on property worth up to 3,000,000 leva
				and a 25% <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1047" type="subject">duty</term> on property worth over that
				amount.</p>
			<pb n="2" facs="EHRI-DR-19410714-IT_02.jpg"/>
			<p>As stated in Art. 3 of this law, the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1047" type="subject">duty</term> has
				to be paid both by <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> having <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/732800/republic-of-bulgaria.html">Bulgarian</placeName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1147" type="subject">citizenship</term> and by <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1149" type="subject">foreign</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term>, whether settled or not in the Country,
				who own movable or real property in Bulgaria.</p>
			<p>A delegation of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Israelite</term> fellow-citizens who
				live here came to the R. Legation to invoke protection, in order to be exempt from the said extraordinary contribution.</p>
			<p>However, the <term ref="#ehri_dr_italo_bulgarian_trade_and_navigation_treaty" type="subject">Italo-Bulgarian Trade and Navigation
					Treaty</term> of <date when="1934">1934</date>, which is still in force and, as we know, contains settlement clauses in favour of
				the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1147" type="subject">citizens</term> of one Country in the other,
				stipulates (Art. 5) in the matter of internal <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1047" type="subject"
					>taxation</term> that they shall receive the same treatment as nationals.</p>
			<p>It would seem, therefore, that there cannot be on our part any intervention grounded in law, aimed at obtaining for the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Israelite</term> fellow-citizens residing here an
				exemption from the extraordinary contribution required by the said law.</p>
			<p>In any case, the issue has a scope that goes beyond the economic aspect.</p>
			<p>I therefore beg the Ministry to let me know, in view of some action that may be undertaken, how we treat <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1149" type="subject">foreign</term> Israelites in the matter of
				contributions like the one decreed today by the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004295">Bulgarian
					government</orgName>, and to advise me, moreover, if <term ref="ehri_dr_nationalities_bulgarians" type="subject">Bulgarian</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Israelites</term> have been affected or not by
				similar measures.</p>
			<p>Magistrati</p>
		</body>
	</text>
